e cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marguerite de Brucourt was born in 1270, in Brucourt, Calvados, Normandy, France, her father, Guillaume I de Brucourt, was 29 and her mother, Euphémie de Courcy, was 26. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert III de Chanteloup - Seigneur de Chanteloup. She died in 1349, in Manche, Normandy, France, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1270–1349":"1270–1349","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1242–1280":"1242–1280","1245–1280":"1245–1280","1349":"1349","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1242":"1242","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","après 1280":"pärast 1280","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","Brucourt, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Chandeloup, Manche, Normandie, France":"Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, France":"Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1270–1349":"1270–1349","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1242–1280":"1242–1280","1245–1280":"1245–1280","1349":"1349","1300":"1300","1245":"1245","1265":"1265","1242":"1242","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","après 1280":"1280 jälkeen","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","Brucourt, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, Ranska","Chandeloup, Manche, Normandie, France":"Manche, Normandie, Ranska","Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, France":"Brucourt, Calvados, Normandie, Ranska","Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Les Moutiers-Hubert, Calvados, Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1270–1349":"1270–1349","1265–1350":"1265–1350","1300–1372":"1300–1372","1242–1280":"1242–1280","1245–1280":"